## Interaction Contract

- `TxLayoutSkeleton` has no props, events, or slots.
- The component always renders a header, 6 sidebar items, and 8 content lines.
- Content line widths are deterministic and do not depend on runtime randomness.

## Dashboard Data Operations

Use `TxLayoutSkeleton` in detail panes, side summaries, or page-level placeholders to show that a layout is coming; do not use it as a replacement for concrete table rows.

:::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="ComponentsDataOperationsDemo" code-lang="vue" title="Data operations panel" description="Layout skeletons cover side/detail regions while DataTable owns the primary table body."}
---
code: |
  <template>
    <div style="height: 190px;">
      <TxLayoutSkeleton />
    </div>
  </template>
---
:::

